Terminology

Overall Budget - The total amount of money available that has been signed off for use on Majority by top level councillors at the beginning of each year of license.
Project Budget - The amount of money required to complete a project
Project - A proposal for local change put forward by a user or a member of the council
Project proposal - The act of creating a project via majority.

Project approval:
Phase 1 - When the administrator approves a proposed project.
Phase 1 is complete when a user has proposed a project and the administrator has approved it.

Phase 2 - When the users vote on whether they want a project that has been approved by an administrator to be put into effect. This coincides with the end of a specified voting period.
Phase 2 is complete when the vote threshold has been reached.

Voting period - The period of time that a project has been given for users to vote on it.

Vote threshold:
For a project to be successful, it must meet the following criteria
Have been approved by the council administrators
Have been voted on by more than the council’s required percentage of users
Have completed its time period for voting (eg. 2 weeks on the application)

Vote approval threshold:
For a project to be successful, it must meet the following criteria
Have been approved by the council administrators
Have been voted on by more than the council’s required percentage of users
Have completed its time period for voting (eg. 2 weeks on the application)
Have received more “yes” votes than “no’s”

Areas of interest, interests(User) - Category types of local change.
Service sectors(Admin) - Category types of local change.
